3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - This paper touches on the social and organizational aspects of coordinating knowledge work in large-scale agile development programs, which could fall under the category of computers and society. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - This paper discusses the coordination practices used in large-scale agile development programs, which could be relevant to the field of human-computer interaction in terms of designing tools and interfaces to support coordination. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - While not directly related to programming languages, this paper does touch on the practices and mechanisms used to coordinate knowledge work in software development, which could be of interest to the programming languages community in terms of designing languages and tools that support coordination.
